<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-551-662  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 551 662.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  May 28 1990 v218 n22 p11(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>RHC information issue headed for Supreme Court.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mason, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A coalition of computer and communications companies, tradeassociations and consumer and legal groups wants the US SupremeCourt to overturn a US appeals court ruling requiring US DistrictJudge Harold Greene to reconsider his 1987 ban against Bellregional holding companies (RHCs) providing information services.andO;Coalition attorneys petitioned the Washington, DC, Court ofAppeals to delay the order to Greene pending its review by theSupreme Court.andP;  The petition to the Supreme Court will be enteredwithin 30 days, but the court will be recessed between June andOct of 1990.andP;  The appeals court had ordered Greene to 'use a lessdemanding standard' and consider only the public interest whenreviewing the issue of RHCs entering the information servicesbusiness, as neither of the original Modified Final Judgementparties, AT and T or the Justice Dept, contested the restriction.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Antitrust LawsCourt CasesBell Regional Holding CompaniesUnited States. Supreme Court.andO;Person:    Greene, Harold (cases).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>